items.title: Porcupine
items.description:
Dan King Alaskan Photography posted a photo:

One of my favorite small creatures to photgraph is the porcupine. They are a gentle animal with a face that is soft and cute. This porcupine was spotted near the Wrangell-St. Elias National Park.
Was able to get the ground level compostion by kneeling down on my knee, the porcupine was elevated just a bit from where I was at.
Contrary to popular belief, the porcupine does not throw quills. They are non aggressive and will gladly waddle away from danger.
